<br>
You can go with 4+ delay blades and still be spec'd in the weapon type for big backstabs, or you can go with quick 2.3ish delay blades for the quick second hit so you can stun them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utiejinnie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tiejinnie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/31/02 11:31:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1979.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Help!! blades or pierce? for Nightshade</span><hr size=1> I've gone Blades, cos I like the higher short-duration dmg returns I get.<br>
<br>
Using a Gem Encrusted Claw (13.1/2.7 - 90%) Blade-type, I was able to pull 528dmg PA on green/blue sitting casters/archers (best was with a 409 Crit attached).<br>
<br>
When I switched to a Shadow Crystal Slicer (15.6/4.4 - 89%) Blade-type, I saw my PA rise incredibly to 600+, with a Crit of ~500 attached). This was almost a 200point dmg increase!<br>
<br>
However, there is a down-side. With this higher dmg scale, I cannot afford long-drawn out fights. It has to end fast. Cos of the 4.4 delay, my Creeping Death takes longer to apply. After PA + CD + 1 or 2 Garrote/AH, they must die, caster/tank included.<br>
<br>
If I take too long, the caster can either a) run away, or b)mez me. However, the Enervating application removes possibility a) from happening. <p><fontcolor="cornflowerblue"><i>Tiejinnie<br>
Lurikeen NightShade<br>
Legion of Avatars - Kay Server</i>
